dquarters atlanta georgia usa area served  us states  key people thomas a fanning chairman president and chief executive officer revenue us billion 00 net income us billion 00 total assets us billion 0 us billion 0  number of employees  00 subsidiaries southern company gas alabama power georgia power gulf power mississippi power southern company services southern linc southern nuclear southern company generation southern power southern telecom powersecure website wwwsoutherncompanycom southern company is an american gas and electric utility holding company based in the southern united states it is headquartered in atlanta georgia with executive offices also located in birmingham alabama the company is currently the second largest utility company in the us in terms of customer base through its subsidiaries it serves  million gas and electric utility customers in nine states southern company’s regulated regional electric utilities serve a 0squaremile 0 km territory with  miles  km of distribution lines contents  overview  history  plant vogtle  plant ratcliffe  partnerships  kemper project controversies  environmental concerns  corrective measures  palliative measures  impact  see also  notes 0 external links overviewedit southern company is one of the largest energy providers in the united states and nd on the fortune  listing of the largest u s corporations it has more than  shareholders nyse so and has been traded since september 0  southern company subsidiaries are building the first new nuclear units in the us in 0 years at plant vogtle near augusta georgia building a stcentury coal facility in kemper county mississippi and are operating or developing renewable solar wind and biomass facilities across the us four retail electric companies alabama power georgia power gulf power and mississippi power serve 0 square miles 0 km in four states southern power serves wholesale electricity customers across the us southern company gas serves utility customers in seven states southern company owns the following companies alabama power  operating company based in birmingham serves the southern twothirds of alabama georgia power  operating company based in atlanta serves all of georgia except four mostly rural counties gulf power  operating company based in pensacola florida serves most of the florida panhandle mississippi power  operating company based in gulfport serves the mississippi gulf coast southern company services  originally named southern services inc  birmingham alabama  common services southern linc  cellular telephone provider  atlanta georgia southern nuclear  engineering and operations for nuclear power plants  birmingham alabama southern company is the majority owner and operator of the farley hatch and vogtle nuclear power plants southern company generation  fossil and hydro operations  birmingham alabama southern power  wholesale power generation  atlanta georgia southern telecom  wholesale fiber optic communications and data services  atlanta georgia southern company gas  serves gas utility customers and operates natural gas pipelines  atlanta georgia powersecure  distributed infrastructure technologies  wake forest north carolina historyedit southern company can be traced back to  when southeastern power  light was formed as a holding company for alabama traction light and power formed 0 the immediate forerunner of alabama power later that year it formed mississippi power as a subsidiary with gulf power following in  in  it merged with georgia power formed 0 in 0 southeastern power  light merged into the commonwealth  southern corporation the new system included five northern companies and six southern companies however in the late 0s commonwealth  southern was dissolved to meet the public utility holding company act of  four of the southern companies—alabama power georgia power gulf power and mississippi power—were deemed to be an integrated system and thus were allowed to remain under common ownership a new holding company southern company was incorporated in delaware on november   and moved to georgia in 0 the year  saw southern company’s first full year of operation in – the company was involved in the dixonyates contract with the atomic energy commission and the associated political controversy in  southern company became the first electric utility holding company in  years to diversify its operations by forming an unregulated subsidiary in january  southern energy inc began official operations as a global energy company growing to serve 0 countries on four continents on april  00 southern company completed the spinoff of southern energy as mirant corporation another southern company subsidiary—southern nuclear—began providing services in  to the systems nuclear power plants in  southern communications services began providing digital wireless communications services to southern companys subsidiaries and also began marketing these services to the public within the southeast as southern linc southern telecom a telecommunications subsidiary of southern company was founded in  southern telecom provides colocation and dark fiber optic lines to network businesses0 on january  00 southern company received final approval from the securities and exchange commission to form southern power a subsidiary to own manage and finance wholesale generating assets in the southeast the new subsidiary targets wholesale customers on july  00 southern company gas received certification from the georgia public service commission to enter the retail gas market after nearly four years of operations the company was sold and customers transferred to cobb emcs newly formed affiliate gas south in 0 southern company acquired powersecure a distributed energy infrastructure technologies company and agl resources which was renamed southern company gas as a result of the agl resources merger southern company doubled its customer base expanded its footprint and broadened the scope of its business by increasing its natural gas presence plant vogtleedit plant vogtle in georgia southern company and its partners are constructing two new units on this site by 00 southern company subsidiaries operate hydroelectric gas coal and nuclear generation sources to generate approximately 00 terawatthours of electricity in 00 coal represented  percent of the companys output followed by nuclear  and natural gas  renewable hydroelectric power represented  percent of southerns generation coalbased generation dropped significantly in 00 from an average of 0 between 00 and 00 in june 00 the united states department of energy awarded an  billion loan guarantee to facilitate the construction of two new nuclear reactors at plant vogtle near augusta georgia a southern company subsidiary georgia power owns  of the current 0 mw facility with coowners oglethorpe power 0 municipal electric authority of georgia  and the city of dalton  the plant is operated by georgia power the  billion construction project is scheduled to be completed by 0 and would double the plants capacity the construction of two  mw reactors has been hailed by energy secretary steven chu as the first new nuclear power plant to break ground in decades it is expected to create up to  jobs during the construction phase and 00 once operational however in march 0 westinghouse electric company who are building the plant filed for chapter  bankruptcy because of  billion of losses from its two us nuclear construction projects the us government had given  billion of loan guarantees on the financing of the four nuclear reactors being built in the us and it is expected a way forward to completing the plant can be agreed plant ratcliffeedit in september 0 the epa introduced new provisions regarding output of carbon emissions in new power facilities the proposed emission limit for new energy sources will be lbs of carbon dioxide per megawatt hour of electricity preemptively recognizing the need for these changes southern company broke g